
Building a Text-to-Speech system for my local language (Yoruba)

I've been concentrating more on developing Deep Learning models to address linguistic issues in Africa since the beginning of this year.

Since almost all (if not all) African languages have limited resources, I chose to concentrate on "Yorùbá."

Over 45 million people worldwide speak "Yorùbá”; a significant tongue that is indigenous to the Yoruba tribe in Nigeria.

Using Yorùbá as the base language
